Preheat oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). In a large bowl combine the cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, chicken soup with rice, mayonnaise, onion and chicken meat. Mix together well. Pour mixture into a 10x10 inch casserole dish. Sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs over the top. Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until it starts to bubble. To Microwave: Put in microwave for 20 minutes.